A federal judge allowed Tyco International Ltd. shareholders to proceed with a class-action lawsuit against the company and former top executives.
L. Dennis Kozlowski and Mark Swartz face retrial for stealing $600 million from Tyco.
The judge dismissed a claim related to fraud allegations but allowed the larceny retrial to continue.
Prosecutors focus on the alleged thefts rather than extravagant purchases.
The case highlights corporate greed and financial manipulation.
Defense lawyers challenge the credibility of former directors and argue against accusations of theft.
The trial sheds light on the inner workings of corporate corruption and legal battles.
